    "author": "Su Shi",
    "translator": "Gil Lehmann; Jacey Chang; Yehudith Dashevsky",
    "poem": "                      赏\n            暮                   花\n      已                                  归\n      时                                                   去\n醒                                                    马\n   微                                   如\n    力                 飞\n      酒\n\n</span>\n\nAs read:\n<span lang= \"zh\">赏花归去马如飞\n去马如飞酒力微\n酒力微醒时已暮\n醒时已暮赏花归",
    "transpoem": "Enjoy\nDusk                Flower\nAlready                        Come\nTime                                Back\nWaking                                Horse\nSlightly                        Like\nImpact                Flying\nWine\n\n\nA Chain Verse \n\nOutside, enjoying the flowers, then coming back\non a horse, running, running, almost flying.\nThe sprightly horse seems like it’s flying;\nthe impact of the wine \nis fading. My drunken\nfog is clearing; \nthe hour \nis already \nlate.\nWhen\n I woke, \nit was already dusk,\nand I’ve come back from enjoying the flowers. \n",
